@@bNorthern Dune Margin@@N~
@@bThe dune margin here is a transitional strip where the Saltglass Reach's compact surface gives way to loose sand built in long ridges by prevailing westerly winds.@@N Glasswalk shoes grip the compressed crests reasonably well, but the slopes between ridges shift unpredictably underfoot. Shell fragments from past beach lines are pressed into the sand in horizontal bands, evidence that the shoreline was once much farther inland. @@bA dusty haze hangs low along the ridge line, thickening to the north where the dunes stack higher before dropping toward the coast.@@N The grinding sound of wind-driven sand is constant here, a fine scouring that leaves exposed metal with a matte finish within hours.
