@@yBank of the Strandline Compact@@N~
@@yThe Bank of the Strandline Compact occupies a reinforced building whose entrance is faced in polished basalt and whose interior is lit by high clerestory windows that illuminate the transaction floor without admitting the street.@@N Gilt-bronze strongboxes are mounted on the wall behind the teller counter, each sealed with the Compact's double-authentication wax and bearing a ledger reference number. @@yThe transaction counter runs the full width of the building and is staffed by clerks who combine the social warmth of archive staff with the numerical precision of instrument calibrators.@@N The bank operates on the Saltweight coinage standard — deposits and withdrawals are calculated against the Tide Ledger Hall's daily rate, and foreign currency is converted at the posted rate before being accepted. A framed statement on the wall reads: ALL DEPOSITS BACKED BY TIDEWALL BOND RESERVE.
