@@yAssessment Courtyard@@N~
@@yThe Assessment Courtyard is the gravitational centre of the Ledger Quarter — a broad open-roofed space where the formal weighing of contested and high-value cargo occurs, and where disputes between the four Ledger Houses are adjudicated before they escalate to the Shoreward House appeal process.@@N Five bronze scales occupy the courtyard's centre, each calibrated against the Tide Ledger Hall's master weight set and each attended by a Compact-licensed assessor whose certification is renewed annually. @@yThe surrounding arcade carries eight relief carvings depicting the eight founding commercial agreements of the Shoreward Compact, each accompanied by the seals of the signatories.@@N Cargo manifests for high-value shipments are presented here for weight verification before the Ledger of Record is closed — a process that occasionally turns confrontational when a declared weight differs significantly from the measured actual. The Storm Ledger Vault is accessible from the eastern side; the Quarantine Ledger complex is further east still. @@lStairs to the Shrine Terrace climb from the northern wall, carved basalt steps that ascend to the upper city above the Ledger Quarter roofline.@@N The courtyard is the only outdoor space in the Ledger Quarter that receives full sun from midday through afternoon, and the bronze scales gleam visibly even from the upper stair level.
