@@yStorm Ledger Vault@@N~
@@yThe Storm Ledger Vault is a sealed bonded storage chamber where high-value cargo is held under weather-risk escrow — goods whose maritime insurance requires physical custody until the bonding authority releases the storm-risk period.@@N The vault is built to the highest structural standard in the Ledger Quarter: stone walls of double thickness, iron-reinforced ceiling, and a floor raised above the courtyard level to prevent flood damage. @@yCargo containers here are sealed with the Storm Ledger's authentication wax and tagged with their escrow reference numbers, bond amounts, and release conditions.@@N The vault is cold — deliberately maintained at lower temperature than the surrounding rooms to reduce the risk of organic cargo spoilage — and the silence here is the particular silence of a space designed to be secure rather than inhabited. A faint smell of the sea comes through the ventilation system, which sources fresh air from a duct that opens at the Tidewall rather than at street level to prevent document ash from entering during any fire elsewhere in the Quarter.
