#14298
@@yQuarantine Isolation Chamber@@N~
@@yThe Quarantine Isolation Chamber is a sealed room of deliberate emptiness — no furniture, no shelving, no organic material of any kind except the containment object at its centre.@@N The object itself is in a basalt crate sealed with Khar'Daan containment script and the Quarantine Ledger's triple-authentication wax: a relic of the funerary tradition whose hazard classification is Class Three, meaning active, unpredictable, and incompletely understood. The cold in this room is the cold of the object rather than the room — it radiates from the sealed crate with a directional quality, stronger on the near side. @@yThe Quarantine Ledger's assessment documentation, visible through the anteroom window, describes the object as an animated hazard-class relic — a containment vessel that was once used to hold and direct funerary energy and has continued to do so after its original context was lost.@@N The monitoring logs record a consistent pattern: the cold intensifies at dawn, stabilises through the day, and diminishes slightly at night. The morning intensification was the first indicator that something had gone wrong with the original containment arrangement. @@RThe chamber walls bear score marks from a previous containment failure — a breach that was resolved but not without damage.@@N Access to this chamber has been restricted since the Class Three designation was applied.
