#14300
@@yLedger Quarter, Eastern Throughway@@N~
@@yThe eastern throughway connects the Quarantine Ledger circuit to the Harbor Approach, a wide passage that marks the transition from the Ledger Quarter's dense archive environment to the open harbor-front zone.@@N The walls here carry the last of the Ledger Quarter's institutional markings — the Shoreward Compact's harbor-seal symbol where the archive zone ends and the harbor zone begins. @@yVentilation improves sharply at this point; the harbor wind reaches the throughway directly through a covered but open-fronted passage that opens onto the Harbor Approach road.@@N The smell shifts from the Ledger Quarter's wax-and-paper composite to the salt, tar, and timber smell of the harbor district.
