#14301
@@yLedger Quarter, Harbor Vestibule@@N~
@@yThe harbor vestibule is the last enclosed space of the Ledger Quarter before the Harbor Gate — a short roofed passage that functions as a weather break between the archive district's temperature-controlled environment and the open harbor front.@@N Notice boards here carry current harbor operational announcements: berth assignments, chain schedule, signal tower messages from the previous day, and the Harbormaster's current cargo priority list. @@yThe vestibule is where Ledger Quarter clerks and Harbor Front workers interact most frequently — passing documentation between the two jurisdictional zones that together manage Mafdet's commercial throughput.@@N The sound of the harbor is clearly audible here — the creak of mooring lines, the percussion of cargo loading, and the overlapping calls of dock workers and ship officers.
