#14302
@@yLedger Quarter, Harbor Approach@@N~
@@yThe Harbor Approach is the final room of the Ledger Quarter and the first room of the transition to the Harbor Front — an in-between space with the institutional weight of the archive district behind it and the working noise of the harbor ahead.@@N @@lThe cove opens fully ahead for the first time since entering the Ledger Quarter — a broad sweep of @@lwater reflecting the sky, the pier timber extending out from the harbor front, and the harbor chain's arc visible in the middle distance.@@N @@yThe Ledger Quarter's carved wall-text ends here abruptly on the western face; the eastern face is bare stone, leaving the transition visually clean.@@N The Harbor Gate is immediately east, and through it the full sensory experience of the working harbor begins.
