@@yLedger Quarter, Northwest Corner@@N~
@@yThe northwest corner of the Ledger Quarter is a quiet administrative zone where the four Ledger Houses maintain their inter-institutional coordination staff — clerks whose job is to ensure that the Houses' overlapping documentary claims do not create unresolvable precedence conflicts.@@N The work here is entirely internal — no public-facing service, no cargo movement, just the careful maintenance of the inter-House agreement framework that keeps the Ledger Quarter's four competing institutions functional. @@yA meeting table dominates the room, surrounded by chairs that show the wear of long, frequently-interrupted sessions.@@N The northwest corner has access to the main Manuscript Passage to the south, making it a convenient hub for document routing between the Tide Ledger Hall and the Assessment Courtyard.
