#14304
@@yLedger Quarter, Southwest Archive Annex@@N~
@@yThe Southwest Archive Annex holds overflow documentation from the Tide Ledger Hall — records that are not currently active but cannot yet be transferred to the Deep Archive due to the ongoing monitoring requirements of the cases they document.@@N The cases here are all resolved but recent — cargo disputes settled within the last three years, weather-risk bonds released within the last two, transit seal violations cleared within the last year. @@yThe annex is a working part of the Ledger Quarter's document cycle rather than a dead archive, and staff access it regularly to retrieve precedent information.@@N The Conversion Scribes' Walk is accessible from the east, which makes the annex a natural complement to the scribes' reference needs.
